description.narrative: Government and key stakeholders (national and decentralized) have an increased capacity to coordinate, plan and monitor interventions in a legal framework to protect children., which contributes to Access To Justice, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children, especially adolescent girls, in vulnerable regions are better protected from violence, abuse, exploitation and harmful practices, including in emergency situations

description.narrative: At the end of 2021, Cameroon’s child protection system has a costed National Multisector Plan of Action 2020 – 2024 and a costed 2020 – 2024 National Multisector Plan of Action for Ending Child Marriage. The child protection system has a strong coordination framework with two national, four regional and 24 divisional coordination platforms and two regional child protection in emergency humanitarian coordination groups. Intersectoral coordination between justice and law enforcement authorities at national and decentralized level has improved. Social workers in UNICEF intervention areas have been trained in case management, data collection and child protection in emergency. | Status:Met | As-of Date:02/02/2022
